Kenya Simbas edged out Uganda Cranes 38-22 for their third consecutive victory in the 2019 World Cup qualifiers at the RFUEA grounds on Saturday. The Simbas failed to get the much needed bonus point victory for the Africa Gold Cup match that doubles up as 2019 Rugby World Cup qualifiers, they successfully retained Elgon Cup 72-38 on aggregate. The Simbas won the first leg of the Elgon Cup 34-16 in Kampala on May 26. More to follow...  